UNITED STATES v. Albert Julian LINDHOLM et al. No. 8493. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 22, 1937. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., of Los Angeles, Cal. James H. O’Neill, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellees.

Before GARRECHT and HANEY, Circuit Judges, and NETERER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; that a judgment of dismissal he filed and entered accordingly; mandate issued forthwith.
